---
import TuiBox from '../TuiBox.astro';
---
<div class="term-pane-header">
  <div class="tui-panel-header"><span>ABOUT</span></div>
</div>
<div class="term-pane" style="overflow-y:auto">

  <h2 class="section-header fg-cyan" >// orcai &mdash; abbs //</h2>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;line-height:2;max-width:700px;margin-bottom:4px">
    Browser-based AI tools charge you for every token spent staring at a loading spinner.
    <span class="fg-purple">orcai</span> runs in your terminal, next to your editor and shell,
    using the models you already have. Local inference, zero cloud markup.
    Your API spend goes to actual work &mdash; not UI overhead.
  </p>

  <TuiBox title="COST & EFFICIENCY">
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-green">LOCAL MODELS</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">Run Ollama on-device. No API call, no bill.<br/>Pull qwen2.5-coder once, run it forever.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-green">TYPED PIPELINES</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">No glue code means no wasted tokens fixing bad output formats.<br/>Steps get what they expect. First time, every time.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-green">BACKGROUND CRON</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">Agents run while you sleep. Wake up to results,<br/>not a context window full of back-and-forth prompting.</div>
    </div>
  </TuiBox>

  <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:13px;line-height:2;max-width:700px;margin-bottom:4px">
    <span class="fg-yellow">BRAIN</span> is context injection. Point it at docs, files, URLs, or code.
    Every agent run gets that context loaded automatically &mdash; your agents know
    your codebase, your standards, your project layout. They stop asking questions
    you've already answered elsewhere.
  </p>

  <TuiBox title="BRAIN, PLUGINS & PRODUCTIVITY">
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-cyan">BRAIN CONTEXT</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">Docs, files, URLs loaded once, reused on every run.<br/>No copy-pasting into chat windows.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-cyan">TMUX SESSIONS</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">Each agent gets its own workspace. Switch mid-pipeline,<br/>kill when done. Terminal stays yours.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-cyan">PLUGIN SYSTEM</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">YAML file pointing at any CLI: rg, jq, ffmpeg, your scripts.<br/>Need more? Implement the gRPC interface in Go.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tui-box-row">
      <div class="tui-box-label fg-cyan">INBOX + FEED</div>
      <div class="tui-box-desc">Every agent run lands in a scrollable inbox.<br/>Review outputs, replay steps, full audit trail.</div>
    </div>
  </TuiBox>

  <p style="color:var(--comment);font-size:11px;margin-top:8px">
    <span class="fg-yellow">&rarr;</span> Press <span class="fg-yellow">3</span> to install &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
    <span class="fg-yellow">5</span> for pipelines &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
    <span class="fg-yellow">8</span> for labs
  </p>
</div>
